# Project Structure Conventions

Because Enroute is a hybrid platform, we must organize the repository cleanly to avoid mixing dependencies. 

## Monorepo Layout
We use a simple directory-based separation. Do not mix `package.json` dependencies between these folders.

```text
/
├── .antigravity/         (AI Coding Rules - DO NOT TOUCH App Code here)
├── apps/
│   ├── mobile/           (React Native Expo App)
│   │   ├── src/          (App Source)
│   │   ├── App.js        (Entry)
│   │   └── package.json  (Mobile deps ONLY)
│   │
│   ├── admin-web/        (React Vite App)
│   │   ├── src/          (Web Source)
│   │   └── package.json  (Web deps ONLY)
│   │
│   └── backend/          (Node.js / Express API)
│       ├── src/          (API Source)
│       └── package.json  (Backend deps ONLY)
│
├── docs/                 (PRDs, Architecture references)
├── documentation.md      (Mandatory Changelog / Progress Tracker)
└── README.md             (Root instructions on how to run all 3 apps)
```

## Naming Conventions
- React Components: PascalCase (e.g., `JobSwipeCard.tsx`)
- Hooks: camelCase (e.g., `useUserData.ts`)
- Utility functions: camelCase (e.g., `calculateDistance.ts`)
- Express Routes: kebab-case (e.g., `/api/v1/cv-analysis`)
- Firebase Collections: lower-case plural (e.g., `users`, `roadmaps`)

## Git & Modifying Code
- Before making sweeping architecture changes, read `overview.mdc` and `tech-stack.mdc`.
- Update `documentation.md` immediately upon completing a task.